Voidface changelog. Newest at the top. Time flows downward.


Voidface 0.0.16 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R5.4a: ONNX export for the shipped generator

    The generator can now be exported to a portable format. ONNX
    Runtime consumes it on Windows and Linux; ONNX Runtime Web
    consumes it in the browser demo with the WebGPU execution
    provider. CoreML export for Apple Silicon lands in R5.4b.

    New:

    * src/voidface/export/onnx.py — export_generator_to_onnx(
        generator, output_path, example_resolution=256, opset=17,
        dynamic_axes=True) — thin wrapper around torch.onnx.export
      that traces the generator on CPU at a fixed example
      resolution and marks batch/height/width as dynamic axes so a
      single .onnx file serves every input size. Opset 17 by default
      — broadly supported by ONNX Runtime, and includes GridSample
      for future R5.5 semantic-warp experiments.

    Dep footprint:

    * onnx and onnxruntime pinned in [export]. Intel-Mac
      compatibility ceiling on onnxruntime: <1.20. coremltools
      constrained to Apple Silicon macOS (arm64) — Intel Macs use
      the ONNX path.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_onnx_export.py — 3 tests:
        - Export produces a non-empty .onnx file at the target path.
        - ONNX Runtime output matches the PyTorch reference to
          within 1e-4 atol / rtol (parity check).
        - dynamic_axes=True produces a graph that traces at 32x32
          but runs correctly at 64x64.
    * Suite is 72 tests, all passing.

    What R5.4a explicitly does NOT ship:

    * ORT-Web .ort conversion for the browser build (R5.4c).
    * CoreML .mlpackage export (R5.4b — coremltools is Apple Silicon
      only, so this session cannot exercise it).
    * int8 quantization (R5.4d — reduces the shipped file from ~21 MB
      fp32 to ~5.5 MB int8; requires a small calibration corpus).


Voidface 0.0.15 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R5.3b: voidface train CLI subcommand

    The training loop is now one command away. `voidface train
    <config.toml>` wires together FolderImageDataset, DataLoader,
    CompositeLoss, EotSampler, RestorerSampler, and train_generator
    from a single TOML file — the same shape every prior smoke
    config uses so training runs are reproducible from disk.

    New:

    * tools/cli/voidface_cli/main.py — new `train` subcommand plus
      _cmd_train() and _build_targets() helpers. TOML sections:
        [experiment]  name, seed, steps, log_every, checkpoint_every,
                      checkpoint_dir
        [data]        directory, resolution, batch_size, augment
        [optim]       learning_rate, weight_decay, epsilon_frac,
                      eot_samples
        [loss.perceptual]  lpips_weight, tv_weight
        [targets.*]   enabled + weight per surrogate
        [restorers]   name = weight pairs for the RestorerSampler
    * samples/configs/train_r5_smoke.toml — reference config that
      exercises the CLI wiring without any external weight downloads
      (all targets disabled, restorer = identity, TV-only loss).
      Real training configs enable the target subset the researcher
      cares about.

    `voidface train --help` renders. `voidface train samples/configs/
    train_r5_smoke.toml --device cpu` runs the loop against
    samples/images/ (a synthetic ellipse) and exits cleanly.

    Tests:

    * Suite is 69 tests, all passing. The CLI train path is not
      unit-tested end-to-end because the interesting convergence
      test already lives in tests/unit/test_train_generator.py; a
      CLI wrapper test would either mock every surrogate or pull
      weights, and both erode signal.


Voidface 0.0.14 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R5.3a: face-image dataset pipeline

    train_generator() from R5.2 accepted any batch iterator; this
    commit lands the first concrete iterator that reads real face
    crops off disk. Voidface deliberately does not bundle a dataset
    — users point at their own FFHQ / CelebA-HQ / private-corpus
    directory.

    New:

    * src/voidface/data/datasets.py — two exports:
        - collect_image_paths(directory, recursive=True) — walks a
          directory, returns a sorted list of every .png / .jpg /
          .jpeg / .webp / .bmp file.
        - FolderImageDataset(directory, resolution=256, augment=True,
          recursive=True, seed=None) — torch.utils.data.Dataset. Each
          __getitem__ returns a (3, H, W) float tensor in [0, 1] at
          the requested resolution. Antialias bilinear resize. Random
          horizontal flip when augment=True. Stable ordering across
          instances so training runs are reproducible.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_datasets.py — 6 tests:
        - empty directory raises FileNotFoundError,
        - non-directory input raises NotADirectoryError,
        - iteration order is stable across instances of the same
          directory,
        - each item has shape (3, R, R), float32, [0, 1] range,
        - integrates with torch.utils.data.DataLoader (batches to
          the expected (B, 3, R, R) shape),
        - augment=True actually flips images sometimes (verified with
          a horizontally-asymmetric checker pattern).
    * Suite is 69 tests, all passing.

    What R5.3a explicitly does NOT ship (later):

    * Automatic FFHQ / CelebA-HQ download (out of scope — those
      datasets have their own licenses and consent-of-subjects issues).
    * Face-region cropping / alignment as part of the loader. The R4
      aligner does this on the fly during training when the GFPGAN
      restorer is enabled; pre-cropped datasets can skip alignment
      entirely.
    * Multi-worker DataLoader tuning. Torch's default single-worker
      loop is sufficient for R5.3 experimentation.


Voidface 0.0.13 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R5.2: G training loop (system convergence)

    The whole system converges end-to-end. train_generator() reuses
    every subsystem R1-R4 built — CompositeLoss, EotSampler,
    RestorerSampler, the ensemble targets — and updates the R5.1
    generator's parameters. The synthetic-target training test
    demonstrably reduces the total composite loss across 30 Adam
    steps: this is the first Voidface commit where the shipped
    generator is being trained against the exact same adversarial
    objectives it will face at inference.

    New:

    * src/voidface/core/train.py — train_generator(...) plus
      TrainConfig, TrainStep, TrainResult. Consumes a batch iterator
      lazily so the same interface works for a real FFHQ loader, a
      finite test iterator, or an infinite streaming pipeline.
    * Update path: G.parameters() via Adam (lr=1e-4, weight_decay
      =1e-6). Per-step history of composite loss + per-target
      breakdown + sampled restorer name. Checkpoint dump on a
      configurable interval — writes step number, state_dict, and
      the generator's VoidfaceConfig so a checkpoint can round-trip
      into a fresh Voidface().

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_train_generator.py — 3 tests:
        - training loop runs over 30 batches AND the trailing-5-step
          loss average is meaningfully lower than the leading-5-step
          average (real convergence, not just execution),
        - the loop exits cleanly when the batch iterator exhausts
          before reaching config.steps,
        - a checkpoint written during training loads back into a
          fresh Voidface(config) instance.
    * Suite is 63 tests, all passing.

    What R5.2 explicitly does NOT ship (R5.3):

    * Dataset pipeline (FFHQ / CelebA-HQ loaders, augmentation,
      face-region cropping). train_generator() takes an
      Iterable[Tensor] — any iterator works — so the loop is unblocked
      on the actual dataset landing.
    * Distributed training. Single-GPU baseline first.
    * CLI subcommand `voidface train <config.toml>`. Direct-python
      invocation via train_generator() works today; the CLI wrapper
      is a wiring commit next.
    * Real large-scale training runs. That happens against the
      full 13-target ensemble on cloud GPUs; this session ships the
      infrastructure that enables it, not the checkpoint itself.


Voidface 0.0.12 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R5.1: generator G architecture

    The shipped model lands. Everything up to R4 has been building
    the training system that produces this network's weights; from R5
    onwards we build the network itself and the training loop that
    turns per-image PGD into a single-forward-pass generator.

    New:

    * src/voidface/generator/architecture.py — Voidface(nn.Module),
      the shipped G:
        - Encoder: 4-stage U-Net downsampling with residual
          GroupNorm+GELU blocks. Base channels 16, doubling per stage,
          capped at 384.
        - Bottleneck: two residual blocks + optional self-attention
          (off by default in R5.1 for CoreML export cleanliness).
        - Decoder: mirror encoder with concatenated skip connections.
        - Head: GroupNorm + GELU + 3x3 -> 3-channel output.
        - Delta projection: tanh -> [-epsilon, +epsilon], added to
          input, clamped to [0, 1].
    * VoidfaceConfig dataclass — epsilon, base_channels, num_stages,
      attention_at_bottleneck. Default gives ~5.35 M parameters
      float32, ~21 MB fp32 -> ~5.5 MB int8 quant. Comfortably inside
      the R5 <=15 MB shipping ceiling.
    * Forward accepts an epsilon override so the same trained
      network can serve different perturbation budgets at inference.
    * Input contract enforced: (N, 3, H, W) float in [0, 1] RGB,
      side lengths divisible by 2^num_stages.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_generator.py — 8 tests:
        - Parameter count within the R5 target (3M-12M).
        - Forward preserves (N, 3, H, W) shape and stays in [0, 1].
        - Delta budget: |G(x) - x|_inf <= epsilon at both the config
          default and the forward override.
        - Non-divisible input raises with a clear message.
        - Deterministic: same input, same output on repeat.
        - Gradient flows to every parameter (needed for training).
        - Self-attention variant instantiates and forwards.
    * Suite is 60 tests, all passing.

    What R5.1 explicitly does NOT ship (deferred to R5.2):

    * The training loop that turns per-image PGD into a G-training
      routine. Draft outline is in Documentation/models/generator.md:
      for each step, sample a batch of face crops -> forward through
      G -> compute the same CompositeLoss the PGD kernel already
      uses -> backprop into G's parameters -> save checkpoint.
    * Dataset pipeline (FFHQ / CelebA-HQ) — src/voidface/data/
      currently only has align.py; datasets.py and augment.py are R5.
    * Distributed training. Single-GPU baseline first; DDP after
      R5.2 shows convergence.
    * CoreML and ONNX export. Both are R5.3, once we have trained
      weights to actually export.
    * The trained weight release. R5.4.


Voidface 0.0.11 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.5.2b: GFPGAN restorer in the bilevel loop (R4 HEADLINE)

    The real face restorer is now in the training loop. Every
    off-the-shelf face-swap and nudify pipeline in 2025-2026 runs
    GFPGAN or CodeFormer as a mandatory final step; a Voidface delta
    that survives it is a delta that survives the actual attack, not
    just the pre-restorer proxy we have been optimizing against
    through R3.

    New:

    * src/voidface/models/restorers/gfpgan.py — GfpganRestorer.
      Satisfies the Restorer protocol: (N, 3, H, W) [0, 1] in ->
      same shape and range out. Pipeline:

          x  ->  RetinaFace     (landmarks)
             ->  align_faces    (5-pt similarity, differentiable)
             ->  GFPGANv1Clean  (aligned 512x512 crop, [-1, 1])
             ->  denorm + clamp ([0, 1])
             ->  unalign_paste  (inverse transform + feathered blend)

      Reuses the RetinaFace instance already loaded by the training
      loop for the detector suppression target — no second detector
      forward, no duplicated network.
    * Weight source: TencentARC/GFPGANv1 (GFPGANv1.4.pth, 348 MB).
      Fetched via huggingface_hub. Legacy 'params_ema' vs
      'state_dict' vs raw pickle shapes handled at load time.
    * Fallback to identity restore per batch element when the
      detector reports below-threshold face confidence. Silent
      fallback would hide detector failures; we warn and pass-through.
    * The R4 CEO critic requirement — the restorer sees an
      FFHQ-aligned crop, not a raw off-distribution frame — is
      structurally satisfied by the aligner from R4.5.2a.

    CLI:

    * 'gfpgan' added to --restorers. Weight defaults to 1.0 per entry.
      Auto-loads the RetinaFace detector for landmarks if the user
      did not explicitly select the 'detector' target.
    * Documented recommended R4 mix: 'identity:0.1,sd15-vae:0.3,
      gfpgan:0.6' — the CEO-critic distribution that pushes the
      generator to survive the actual attacker pipeline most of the
      time while still working against un-restored bulk scrapers.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_gfpgan_restorer_smoke.py — 4 tests using stub
      RetinaFace + stub GFPGANv1Clean to keep CI off the 348 MB
      download:
        - Restorer protocol satisfied (structural typing check).
        - Input shape preserved through the detect -> align -> forward
          -> unalign round-trip.
        - Gradient flows through the whole bilevel pipeline
          (image -> landmarks -> align -> gfpgan -> unalign -> loss).
        - Fallback works when the detector reports no face above
          threshold.
    * Suite is 52 tests, all passing.

    What R4.5.2b DOES NOT yet include (R4.5.2c, next commit):

    * The bilevel LPIPS term LPIPS(gfpgan(x+delta), gfpgan(x_clean))
      in the composite loss. The CEO critic requested this and the
      current commit sets up all the infrastructure — the restorer
      IS invoked on both the perturbed and clean paths already inside
      the R2 CompositeLoss; the missing piece is adding an explicit
      perceptual term on the restored outputs, not just per-target
      adversarial losses.
    * SHA-256 integrity gate on the GFPGANv1.4.pth download.
      Documented as a risk carried into R5 self-hosting per the
      packaging critic.
    * MPS gradient checkpointing across the 8 StyleGAN2 decoder
      blocks. Guardrail for Intel-Mac emulated MPS 6.77 GB ceiling.

    R4 is now:

    * R4.1 ✅ shared VAE loader
    * R4.2 ✅ SDXL VAE
    * R4.3 ✅ real ArcFace
    * R4.4 ✅ real RetinaFace + stand-in purge
    * R4.5.1 ✅ vendored GFPGAN architecture
    * R4.5.2a ✅ differentiable 5-point aligner
    * R4.5.2b ✅ GfpganRestorer + CLI wiring (this commit)
    * R4.5.2c — bilevel LPIPS + SHA gate + MPS grad checkpoint (next)
    * R4.6 ✅ OpenAI CLIP ViT-B/32


Voidface 0.0.10 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.5.2a: differentiable 5-point aligner

    Prerequisite for the GfpganRestorer in R4.5.2b. The R4 CEO critic
    flagged that face restorers are trained on tightly-cropped
    FFHQ-aligned face crops and that feeding them off-distribution
    unaligned inputs produces a gradient signal that does not reflect
    what an attacker's real pipeline sees. This module gives
    R4.5.2b's restorer a differentiable path from a full RGB image +
    5 landmarks to an FFHQ-canonical 512x512 aligned crop, and back.

    New:

    * src/voidface/data/align.py — three public functions and one
      container:
        - FFHQ_LANDMARKS_512 constant: the same 5-point template
          GFPGAN, CodeFormer, and Real-ESRGAN-face-enhance were
          trained against.
        - estimate_similarity_transform(source, target) — batched
          least-squares fit for (scale, rotation, translation) via
          SVD. Reflection-corrected so det(R) = +1.
        - align_faces(image, landmarks, output_size=512) — returns an
          AlignedFace(crop, transform) named-container.
          Grid-sample-based warp; differentiable through the input
          image and landmarks.
        - unalign_paste(original, restored_crop, transform,
          feather_pixels=32) — pastes the aligned restored crop back
          into the original image space via inverse similarity
          transform + feathered alpha blend. Also differentiable.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_align.py — identity transform recovered on
      same-in-same-out, pure translation recovered accurately, shape
      contract enforced, gradient flows through the full pipeline
      (grad-check), and the align-then-unalign round-trip
      reconstructs the input to within a small blend tolerance.
    * Suite is 48 tests, all passing.

    What R4.5.2b will build on this (next commit):

    * GfpganRestorer(Restorer) that: reuses a RetinaFace instance for
      landmarks, aligns via align_faces, forwards the aligned crop
      through the vendored GFPGANv1Clean (weights fetched with a
      SHA-256 gate), denormalizes [-1, 1] -> [0, 1] + clamp, then
      pastes back via unalign_paste. Full Restorer-protocol
      compliance: (N, 3, H, W) in -> (N, 3, H, W) out.
    * RestorerSampler mix adjustment: identity 0.10, sd15-vae 0.30,
      gfpgan 0.60 (per CEO critic — restorer is the headline).
    * Bilevel LPIPS(gfpgan(x+delta), gfpgan(x_clean)) term in the
      composite loss.
    * MPS gradient checkpointing over the 8 StyleGAN2 decoder blocks.


Voidface 0.0.9 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.6: OpenAI CLIP ViT-B/32 surrogate

    First CLIP-family target lands. Every 2024-2026 personalization
    pipeline (IP-Adapter, InstantID, PhotoMaker, PuLID) conditions on
    a CLIP-family image embedding. This target reproduces the shape
    of that conditioning path in the ensemble.

    New target:

    * src/voidface/models/clip/openclip.py — OpenClip(nn.Module) —
      differentiable OpenAI CLIP ViT-B/32 image encoder. Loaded via
      transformers.CLIPVisionModel from openai/clip-vit-base-patch32
      (~150 MB). Input adaptation: antialias resize to 224, CLIP
      per-channel mean/std normalization (0.481/0.458/0.408 mean,
      0.269/0.261/0.276 std). Output: L2-normalized 768-D pooled CLS
      embedding.
    * TargetSpec name 'openclip-vit-b-32', family 'clip'.

    Dep footprint:

    * pyproject.toml — transformers added to [train]. Capped below
      4.45 on Intel Mac (torch 2.2 compat). Unconstrained elsewhere.
    * open_clip_torch NOT added per the R4 packaging critic — its
      transitive fanout (timm + ftfy + regex + sentencepiece) would
      collide with the Intel-Mac huggingface_hub ceiling.

    CLI wiring:

    * 'openclip' added to --targets. Weight 0.10 in the composite;
      documented as a bootstrap surrogate — cross-scale attack
      transfer to the H/14 encoders IP-Adapter actually uses is only
      20-40%, so this weight stays modest until R5 adds ViT-L/14.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_openclip_smoke.py — module import, spec check,
      monkey-patched wrapper test that verifies (a) antialias resize
      to 224, (b) CLIP mean/std normalization brings channels to ~0
      when the input equals the mean, (c) output is L2-normalized
      768-D.
    * Suite is 42 tests, all passing.

    R4 status:

    * R4.1 ✅ shared VAE loader
    * R4.2 ✅ SDXL VAE
    * R4.3 ✅ real ArcFace
    * R4.4 ✅ real RetinaFace
    * R4.5.1 ✅ vendored GFPGAN architecture (facexlib-free)
    * R4.5.2 — GfpganRestorer + aligner + bilevel LPIPS (deferred)
    * R4.6 ✅ OpenAI CLIP ViT-B/32 (this commit)


Voidface 0.0.8 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.5.1: vendored GFPGAN architecture (facexlib-free)

    The vendoring half of the R4 headline. The GFPGANv1Clean and
    StyleGAN2GeneratorClean architectures ship in-tree with the two
    basicsr coupling points (ARCH_REGISTRY, default_init_weights)
    shimmed inline. Zero new pip deps. The transitive
    gfpgan -> basicsr -> facexlib -> numba chain that has blocked
    every prior Python-3.12 attempt at a real face restorer is now
    broken.

    Vendored files:

    * src/voidface/models/restorers/_gfpgan/__init__.py — package
      docstring.
    * src/voidface/models/restorers/_gfpgan/_basicsr_shims.py —
      ARCH_REGISTRY no-op decorator and inlined default_init_weights
      (Kaiming init for Conv2d and Linear, constant-1 for BatchNorm).
      Sourced from BasicSR (Apache-2.0). Attribution preserved.
    * src/voidface/models/restorers/_gfpgan/stylegan2_clean.py —
      StyleGAN2GeneratorClean from GFPGAN (Apache-2.0). Only import
      lines adjusted to point at _basicsr_shims. No functional
      changes to the arch. State dicts from the upstream v1.4
      release load bit-for-bit.
    * src/voidface/models/restorers/_gfpgan/gfpgan_clean.py —
      GFPGANv1Clean top-level network. Same treatment as above.
    * LICENSES/Apache-2.0-gfpgan.txt — attribution + upstream URL.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_gfpgan_arch_smoke.py — verifies the shims
      import, StyleGAN2GeneratorClean instantiates at a small
      out_size, and GFPGANv1Clean.forward returns
      ``(image, out_rgbs)`` with the expected shapes at 64x64
      resolution from random weights.
    * Suite is 40 tests, all passing.

    What R4.5.1 explicitly does NOT ship (deferred to R4.5.2):

    * GfpganRestorer wrapper class that satisfies the Restorer
      protocol. Weight download from the official v1.4 release
      (348 MB torch pickle) with SHA-256 gate.
    * The RetinaFace-landmark-based aligner that the CEO critic
      flagged as mandatory ("off-distribution unaligned inputs
      produce a gradient signal that does not reflect what the
      attacker sees"). This lands as a dedicated aligner module
      under data/align.py using the landmarks that R4.4's RetinaFace
      wrapper already returns in TargetOutputs.aux.
    * The bilevel LPIPS term LPIPS(gfpgan(x+delta), gfpgan(x_clean))
      in the composite loss (CEO critic requirement).
    * RestorerSampler mix adjustment to identity:0.10, sd15-vae:0.30,
      gfpgan:0.60. Currently the default mix is identity:0.3,
      sd15-vae:0.7; unchanged in this commit.
    * MPS memory guard (gradient checkpointing over the eight
      StyleGAN2 decoder blocks) — pre-decided per the CEO critic
      but not yet wired.

    Rationale for splitting R4.5 into two commits: the vendored code
    is 692 LoC of correct, testable, dep-free architecture that
    unblocks R4.5.2 without carrying the risk of the weight-load +
    aligner + bilevel-loss integration in the same commit. R4.5.2
    is the actual bilevel-headline commit; R4.5.1 makes it possible.


Voidface 0.0.7 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.4: real RetinaFace-R50 + purge stand-ins

    The face-detector target moves from a Phase R1 MTCNN-PNet stand-in
    to real RetinaFace — the SSH/FPN detector InsightFace ships in the
    buffalo_l bundle and that every mainstream face-swap workflow
    reaches for. Suppressing RetinaFace's face-present logit is
    Voidface's single most valuable adversarial signal, because the
    detector is the one pipeline stage no face restorer can compensate
    for.

    Vendored architecture:

    * src/voidface/models/detectors/_retinaface_arch.py — RetinaFace-R50
      arch vendored from biubug6/Pytorch_Retinaface (MIT). SPDX header
      + modification note. Modifications:
        - Removed the MobileNetV1(0.25) backbone path; we only ship the
          ResNet-50 variant.
        - Removed the `phase` argument from RetinaFace.forward. Voidface
          ALWAYS returns raw pre-softmax classification logits so the
          TargetOutputs.logits field is truthful (R4 correctness
          critic caught the phase-gated softmax ambiguity).
        - Type-annotated, ruff-formatted.
      State dicts from yakhyo/retinaface-pytorch load bit-for-bit.
    * LICENSES/MIT-biubug6-retinaface.txt — full MIT license text.

    Wrapper (models/detectors/retinaface.py):

    * RetinaFace(nn.Module) — differentiable RetinaFace-R50 detector.
    * Weight fetch from yakhyo/retinaface-pytorch (109 MB) via
      huggingface_hub.
    * DataParallel-prefix state-dict remap (strip ``module.``).
    * Input adaptation matches upstream training: [0, 1] RGB ->
      antialias-resize to 640 -> multiply by 255 -> BGR flip ->
      subtract per-channel mean (104, 117, 123). No /255 divide.
    * Output: TargetOutputs.logits is (N, num_anchors, 2) RAW
      pre-softmax; face-present logit is [..., 1]. TargetOutputs.aux
      carries bbox_regressions and landmarks for later use by the
      GFPGAN aligner in R4.5.

    Purge of Phase R1 stand-ins:

    * models/detectors/mtcnn_pnet.py — deleted.
    * models/recognizers/facenet.py — deleted.
    * pyproject.toml — facenet-pytorch removed from [train]. The two
      real surrogates (Arcface, RetinaFace) both fetch weights via
      huggingface_hub without any face-specific pip dep.

    CLI:

    * 'detector' target now loads RetinaFace instead of MtcnnPnet.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_retinaface_smoke.py — module import, spec, arch
      instantiation + forward-to-expected-shape, a specific
      raw-logits-not-softmax'd assertion (per R4 critic), and a
      monkey-patched wrapper test that verifies the exact upstream
      pixel prep: BGR flip, x255, per-channel mean subtraction with
      pixel values in the right range.
    * Suite is 37 tests, all passing.

    R4 recap so far:

    * R4.1 ✅ shared VAE bypass loader
    * R4.2 ✅ SDXL VAE surrogate
    * R4.3 ✅ real ArcFace / IResNet-100
    * R4.4 ✅ real RetinaFace-R50 (this commit)
    * R4.5 — GFPGAN in the bilevel loop (headline) — next
    * R4.6 — OpenCLIP ViT-B/32 — after R4.5


Voidface 0.0.6 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.3: real ArcFace / IResNet-100

    The face-recognizer target moves from a Phase R1 FaceNet stand-in
    to real ArcFace — the identity encoder that every off-the-shelf
    face-swap and personalization pipeline (SimSwap, InSwapper,
    FaceShifter, HifiFace, InstantID, PhotoMaker, IP-Adapter) uses as
    its conditioner.

    Vendored architecture:

    * src/voidface/models/recognizers/_iresnet.py — IResNet-100 backbone
      vendored from InsightFace's arcface_torch reference (Apache-2.0).
      Full SPDX header + modification note. Bit-for-bit state-dict
      compatibility with upstream weights. Modifications:
        - Removed CUDA-only torch.cuda.amp.autocast in forward.
        - Removed the placeholder raise in _iresnet's pretrained branch.
        - Type-annotated and formatted to Voidface style. No functional
          changes to the architecture.
    * LICENSES/Apache-2.0-insightface.txt — the full Apache-2.0 license
      text ships with the source and every wheel per the R4.1 sdist
      change.

    Wrapper (models/recognizers/arcface.py):

    * Arcface(nn.Module) — differentiable IResNet-100 identity encoder.
      Weight fetch from minchul/cvlface_arcface_ir101_webface4m (249 MB
      torch pickle) through huggingface_hub.
    * State-dict key remapping strips cvlface's wrapper prefixes
      (model.*/backbone.*/net.*) so the checkpoint aligns with the
      vendored arch bit-for-bit.
    * Input adaptation matches the arcface_torch training pipeline
      exactly: [0,1] RGB -> antialias resize to 112 -> BGR channel flip
      (upstream trained on cv2 BGR pixels; a naive RGB feed silently
      gives wrong embeddings) -> normalize to [-1, 1].
    * Output: L2-normalized 512-D embedding. Plugs into the existing
      arcface_identity_loss unchanged.

    CLI wiring:

    * tools/cli/voidface_cli/main.py — 'recognizer' target now loads
      Arcface instead of Facenet. Facenet stand-in remains in the
      tree at models/recognizers/facenet.py for reference; the
      facenet-pytorch dep is kept until R4.4 lands (MtcnnPnet still
      uses it).

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_arcface_smoke.py — module import, spec check,
      IResNet-100 instantiation (65M params), (N, 3, 112, 112) ->
      (N, 512) forward shape, and a monkey-patched wrapper test that
      verifies (a) the BGR flip is applied, (b) the [-1, 1] normalize
      is applied, and (c) the output embedding is unit-norm.
    * Suite is 33 tests, all passing.

    Known limits carried forward:

    * ArcFace weights are trained on WebFace4M which carries academic/
      non-commercial-research terms — documented in CREDITS as a
      surrogate role. R5 self-hosts these weights to a Voidface-owned
      HF repo (per R4 packaging critic).
    * torch.load(weights_only=False) accepted for cvlface's .pt
      pickle. R5 adds a SHA-256 integrity gate + safetensors mirror.
    * MtcnnPnet still uses facenet-pytorch. Removed in R4.4 alongside
      the real RetinaFace surrogate.


Voidface 0.0.5 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R4.1 + R4.2: shared VAE loader, SDXL VAE

    Preparation and second VAE-family target for the R4 ensemble
    expansion. Non-controversial commits so the harder R4.3-R4.5 work
    (real ArcFace, real RetinaFace, real face restorer in bilevel
    loop) lands on a clean base.

    R4.1 — Shared VAE bypass loader:

    * src/voidface/models/vaes/_diffusers_loader.py — new module
      exposing ``load_autoencoder_kl(model_id, device, subfolder=...)``
      and ``normalize_legacy_attention_keys(state_dict)``. Wraps
      huggingface_hub.hf_hub_download + safetensors.torch.load_file
      + AutoencoderKL(**config), plus the legacy attention key rename
      (query/key/value/proj_attn -> to_q/to_k/to_v/to_out.0).
    * src/voidface/models/vaes/sd15.py — refactored to import the
      helper. Loader duplication removed; behavior unchanged.
    * pyproject.toml — LICENSES/ added to sdist include list (per the
      R4 packaging critic; upcoming vendored files ship license
      headers to LICENSES/ so downstream tarballs must include them).

    R4.2 — SDXL VAE surrogate:

    * src/voidface/models/vaes/sdxl.py — SdxlVae, mirrors sd15.py's
      shape verbatim but pulls madebyollin/sdxl-vae-fp16-fix (334 MB)
      through the shared loader. Preferred input size 256 for
      Intel-Mac MPS headroom. Latent scaling factor 0.13025.
    * SDXL VAE encoder attacks transfer to SD 1.5 VAE at only ~30%
      per the R4 research; this is a genuinely separate ensemble
      target, not a weight-swap of Sd15Vae.
    * All bilinear resizes use antialias=True per the model-
      correctness critic.
    * CLI — 'sdxl-vae' added to --targets. Weight 0.15 in the default
      composite. Auto-loads no restorer (identity by default).

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_sdxl_vae_smoke.py — module import, spec check,
      monkey-patched AutoencoderKL to exercise the wrapper wiring
      without pulling 334 MB in CI.
    * Suite is 29 tests, all passing.

    What R4.1 + R4.2 explicitly do NOT ship:

    * Real ArcFace (R4.3), real RetinaFace (R4.4), GFPGAN in bilevel
      loop (R4.5 — the actual R4 headline), OpenCLIP ViT-B/32 (R4.6).
      Each has a research plan and a critic-approved integration
      sketch in the Phase R4 workflow output; they land in follow-up
      commits.


Voidface 0.0.4 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R3: bilevel loop, SD-VAE restorer

    The bilevel objective becomes real. A restorer is now sampled per
    PGD step from a weighted distribution and every ensemble target
    sees restorer(adversarial). The first real restorer target is the
    Stable Diffusion 1.5 VAE round-trip, which strips high-frequency
    information the encoder cannot preserve — a fair stand-in for
    the DiffPure-family strip attacks that broke every prior
    adversarial-cloaking tool.

    New pieces:

    * src/voidface/models/restorers/sd_vae.py — Sd15VaeRestorer.
      Reuses the AutoencoderKL from the Sd15Vae encoder target
      (shared weights, no duplicated download). Runs decode(encode(x))
      and rescales back to the input resolution. Dynamic sizing (round
      to stride 8, cap at 512) so low-memory devices do not OOM.
    * src/voidface/models/restorers/sampler.py — RestorerSampler.
      Weighted per-step sampling over a list of (Restorer, weight)
      pairs; zero-weight entries dropped; empty and all-zero
      configurations raise cleanly. Deterministic seed hook.
    * src/voidface/models/vaes/sd15.py — Sd15Vae exposes
      `underlying_vae` and `device` properties so the restorer can
      share the loaded weights.

    Core changes:

    * src/voidface/core/pgd.py — run_pgd accepts an optional
      restorer_sampler. When provided, one restorer is drawn per step
      and forwarded to CompositeLoss.compute. Sampled restorer name is
      recorded on every PgdStep for post-hoc analysis.
    * PgdStep gains a `restorer` field defaulting to "identity" so R1
      and R2 result records stay valid.

    CLI:

    * tools/cli/voidface_cli/main.py — new `--restorers` flag.
      Accepts "name[:weight],..." with `identity` and `sd15-vae`
      currently supported. `sd15-vae` auto-loads the VAE target if the
      user forgot to enable it. Weight defaults to 1.0 per entry.
      Example: `--restorers "identity:0.3,sd15-vae:0.7"`.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_restorer_sampler.py — single-option always
      samples; weight ratio respected under 2000 draws; zero-weight
      entries dropped; empty and all-zero configurations raise;
      probabilities map normalizes.
    * tests/unit/test_pgd_with_restorer_sampler.py — run_pgd draws
      both restorers across 20 steps when the sampler is balanced;
      un-configured runs record "identity" throughout.
    * Suite is 27 tests, all passing.

    Verification (Intel Mac CPU, 256x256 synthetic input, 3 steps,
    seed 0, restorers = identity:0.3, sd15-vae:0.7):

    * Every PGD step routed through the SD-VAE round-trip restorer.
    * Total loss 8.96 -> 7.66 (14% drop).
    * VAE latent loss 32.55 -> 27.33 (16% drop through the restorer,
      demonstrating the delta survives VAE compression).
    * PSNR 33.04 dB (up from 27.85 dB in R1 — perceptibility gains
      from LPIPS + TV plus the additional constraints from routing
      through the restorer).

    Known limits carried forward:

    * The SD-VAE round-trip is not a face restorer. It is a
      "diffusion purification" stand-in. Real face restorers (GFPGAN,
      CodeFormer, Real-ESRGAN) still land in Phase R4.
    * Detector and recognizer remain the Phase R1 stand-ins.
    * Trained generator G is not yet built.
    * CPU-only for the bilevel run on Intel Mac; MPS backend OOMs on
      the VAE decode step. Higher-VRAM Apple Silicon devices should
      run on MPS without changes.


Voidface 0.0.3 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R2: restorer abstraction, VAE target, LPIPS

    The bilevel-loss infrastructure lands and the ensemble grows from
    (detector, recognizer) to (detector, recognizer, VAE) with a real
    perceptual constraint.

    Restorer subsystem:

    * src/voidface/models/restorers/base.py — Restorer protocol and
      RestorerSpec dataclass. Every restorer is a differentiable
      image-to-image transform with the canonical layout preserved.
    * src/voidface/models/restorers/identity.py — pass-through
      restorer. Included in the restorer sample distribution so the
      generator still learns to defeat un-restored pipelines.
    * core/loss.py — CompositeLoss.compute accepts an optional
      restorer. When passed, every target sees restorer(adversarial)
      instead of adversarial; clean side is never restored.

    New ensemble target family — VAEs:

    * src/voidface/models/vaes/sd15.py — Stable Diffusion 1.5 VAE
      encoder, loaded from stabilityai/sd-vae-ft-mse. Includes a
      bypass loader that works around a diffusers 0.29 + torch 2.2
      compatibility issue and a legacy-key remapper for the pre-
      refactor attention weights.
    * core/loss.py — vae_gray_latent_loss(perturbed, target_data=...)
      drives ||E(x+delta) - E(gray)||^2, normalized per-latent-element.
    * VAE surrogate accepts variable input size (rounded to stride 8,
      capped at 512) so low-memory MPS devices do not OOM.

    Perceptual metrics:

    * src/voidface/eval/perceptual.py — PSNR, SSIM (depthwise Gaussian
      window), and LPIPS loader. All accept the canonical layout.
    * CompositeLoss accepts an optional LPIPS callable for the
      perceptual budget; wired into the CLI as the default.
    * `voidface report` prints PSNR + SSIM + L-inf.

    CLI expansion:

    * tools/cli/voidface_cli/main.py — `--targets` selects which
      subset of the ensemble to use (`detector`, `recognizer`, `vae`).
      Weights renormalize automatically. `--no-lpips` disables the
      perceptual constraint for faster experiments.

    Dependencies:

    * Added diffusers (capped below 0.30 on Intel Mac) and
      huggingface-hub for the VAE.
    * facexlib pivot avoided; we bypass diffusers' state-dict loader
      to keep torch 2.2 support intact.

    Tests:

    * tests/unit/test_restorer_identity.py — IdentityRestorer
      satisfies the Restorer protocol and preserves inputs bit-for-bit.
    * tests/unit/test_perceptual.py — PSNR and SSIM basic properties
      (equal images -> inf / 1.0; more noise -> lower PSNR).
    * tests/unit/test_composite_loss.py — signature dispatch (single
      arg vs pair vs target_data kwarg); zero-weight targets skipped;
      IdentityRestorer wrapping matches unwrapped loss.
    * Suite is 19 tests, all passing.

    Verification (Intel Mac Rosetta MPS, 256x256 synthetic input):

    * (detector, recognizer): recognizer loss 1.98 -> 0.03 in 20
      steps, SSIM 0.60 without LPIPS.
    * (detector, recognizer, vae) with LPIPS: recognizer engaged at
      1.85, VAE latent MSE 58 -> 30 (48% drop) in 3 steps, SSIM 0.96.
      Perceptual invisibility is meaningfully better with LPIPS.

    Known limits (updated in Documentation/limits.md):

    * Detector and recognizer are still Phase R1 stand-ins
      (mtcnn-pnet, facenet-vggface2). Real RetinaFace + ArcFace lands
      in Phase R3.
    * No real face restorer (GFPGAN, CodeFormer, Real-ESRGAN) yet;
      the identity restorer is the only sampled instance. Real
      restorers are the Phase R3 headline.
    * SDXL, Flux VAE, OpenCLIP, SigLIP, DINOv2 land alongside the
      real detectors and restorers in Phase R3.
    * Trained generator G is not yet built; the CLI still runs
      per-image PGD.


Voidface 0.0.2 — 2026-07-05 — Phase R1: end-to-end PGD baseline

    First working adversarial pipeline. `voidface protect <image>` runs
    a real PGD attack against a real face-recognition network and saves
    a perturbed output with the L-infinity budget honored and PSNR
    reported.

    * src/voidface/util/{image,log,config}.py — canonical tensor I/O,
      structlog logger, TOML config loader.
    * src/voidface/core/eot.py — expectation-over-transformation
      sampler with resize and Gaussian blur. Differentiable JPEG and
      the WEBP/AVIF surrogates land in Phase R2.
    * src/voidface/core/loss.py — composite adversarial loss
      (CompositeLoss, LossWeights, LossBreakdown) plus the atomic
      RetinaFace suppression and ArcFace identity terms and a TV
      regularizer.
    * src/voidface/core/pgd.py — reference per-image signed-gradient
      PGD kernel with MI-FGSM momentum, EOT wrapping, and per-step
      history.
    * src/voidface/models/detectors/mtcnn_pnet.py — PNet detector
      surrogate (Phase R1 stand-in; replaced by RetinaFace/SCRFD/
      YuNet/MTCNN in Phase R2).
    * src/voidface/models/recognizers/facenet.py — InceptionResnetV1
      identity encoder surrogate (Phase R1 stand-in; replaced by
      ArcFace/MagFace/AdaFace in Phase R2).
    * tools/cli/voidface_cli/main.py — `protect` and `report`
      subcommands wired end-to-end.
    * facenet-pytorch added as the Phase R1 [train] dependency (both
      P-Net and InceptionResnetV1 auto-download weights on first use).
    * tests/unit/test_pgd_synthetic.py — proves the PGD loop converges
      against a synthetic differentiable target in milliseconds.
    * tests/unit/test_image.py — round-trip and shape tests for the
      canonical tensor I/O layer.
    * samples/images/synthetic_face.png — public-domain smoke target.

    Verified: R1 recognizer loss dropped 97% (1.997 → 0.058) in 20
    PGD steps against a real face-recognition network. L-infinity
    budget held exactly at 12/255.

    Known limits:
    * Detector surrogate is P-Net only; the R2 4-detector ensemble
      is not implemented.
    * VAEs, CLIP-family, and restorers are still unimplemented; the
      bilevel training objective is not yet exercised.
    * Trained generator G is not yet built. This release runs
      per-image PGD, not a single forward pass.


Voidface 0.0.1 — 2026-07-05

    Initial repository scaffold.

    * Established directory layout (src/, Documentation/, tools/, runtime/,
      scripts/, samples/, tests/) mirroring Linux-kernel subsystem
      organization.
    * MIT license (COPYING, LICENSES/MIT.txt).
    * Maintainer file with subsystem ownership (MAINTAINERS).
    * Documentation/coding-style.md — style rules enforced across the tree.
    * Documentation/architecture.md — the high-level design.
    * pyproject.toml with the initial dependency set (PyTorch, torchvision,
      onnx, coremltools; ruff and mypy for lint and type check).
    * Makefile with install / lint / test / bench / docs targets.
    * CI scaffolding under .github/workflows/.
    * No ML code yet. This release is the empty vessel.
